results.name: First differences of A335794.
comment: Position of 6 occurs every 2^(n-1) + 1 for n > 0.
Position of 18 appears to occur according to the tetranacci numbers (cf. A000288): 4, 7, 13, 25, 49, ...
reference: S. M. Ulam, On some mathematical problems connected with patterns of growth of figures, pp. 215-224 of R. E. Bellman, ed., Mathematical Problems in the Biological Sciences, Proc. Sympos. Applied Math., Vol. 14, Amer. Math. Soc., 1962 (see Example 6, page 224).
